  <prompt>
    Build the `ActionEngine.IntegrationTests.StarterTemplates` integration test suite that proves graduation criterion G1: the three starter Templates (Summarize a matter, Send weekly task digest, Find similar matters) author and execute end-to-end via both manual and (where applicable) scheduled invocation paths. Use BFF integration-test harness against a test Dataverse environment with the seeded default playbook.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Spaarke platform engineer with deep BFF (.NET 8 Minimal API) integration-testing experience. Familiar with xUnit + `WebApplicationFactory` patterns, in-memory test substitutes for Dataverse + Azure AI Search, and the existing `AnalysisOrchestrationService` integration-test pattern as reference.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ActionEngine/StarterTemplatesIntegrationTests.cs` exists with at least one integration test per starter Template (3 tests minimum), each:
    1. Authors the Template via solution-source JSON (or fixture loader)
    2. Creates an `sprk_actioninstance` row with parameter values
    3. Dispatches via `/actions/{id}/run` for manual + via `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler` for the scheduled one
    4. Asserts a successful `sprk_actionrun` record with `Status = Completed`
    5. Asserts the Tool dispatch audit chain (ADR-015 Tier 2 hash) wrote at least one entry per Tool invocation
    All tests pass against the test harness. Graduation criterion G1 is verifiable from `dotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~StarterTemplates`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      G1 is the single most user-visible graduation gate — the three starter Templates are the demo surface for MVP acceptance. This test suite codifies the contract: every Template must author + execute end-to-end without manual intervention beyond the in-test gate-approval shim. Test failures here are MVP-blocking.

      The three Templates have different execution shapes:
      - **Summarize a matter** — Deterministic Dataverse query + AI narrative Tool; output to chat surface; no gate
      - **Send weekly task digest** — Cron-triggered; Deterministic query + template-rendered email; `SendEmail` requires gate (use `AutoApproveGateResolver` shim in tests)
      - **Find similar matters** — Hybrid: Azure AI Search semantic + Dataverse hydration; citations rendered to chat
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ActionEngine/StarterTemplatesIntegrationTests.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/ActionOrchestrationService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ActionEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/templates/summarize-matter.json</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/templates/weekly-task-digest.json</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/templates/find-similar-matters.json</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Test substitutes for AI clients MUST be in-memory fakes (no real Azure OpenAI in CI). Mock `IOpenAiClient` + `ISearchClient` per existing AI test patterns.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">Integration tests live in `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Use `WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt;` per existing pattern.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tests MUST assert audit chain writes Tier 2 hash-only entries per Tool dispatch; MUST NOT log verbatim prompt or response content in assertions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-004">Scheduled trigger test MUST exercise `IJobHandler&lt;T&gt;` directly via `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler.HandleAsync(...)` — not by waiting on Service Bus.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No test may persist state across runs; each test creates + tears down its Action + ActionInstance + ActionRun records.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/integration-tests.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/mocking-patterns.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-test-organization.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="WebApplicationFactory integration test" location=".claude/patterns/testing/integration-tests.md">Existing BFF integration-test harness pattern; reuse for AE Template tests.</pattern>
      <pattern name="In-memory AI client substitutes" location=".claude/patterns/testing/mocking-patterns.md">Fake `IOpenAiClient` / `ISearchClient` that returns deterministic shapes — keeps CI offline.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean; load `.claude/constraints/testing.md` + `bff-extensions.md`; verify task 053, 054, 055 (starter Templates) are completed in TASK-INDEX.md.</step>
    <step order="1">Read all knowledge files; study existing AI integration tests in `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` for the `WebApplicationFactory` setup + in-memory client substitute patterns.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ActionEngine/` folder. Add `StarterTemplatesIntegrationTests.cs` with `WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt;` fixture; register fake `IOpenAiClient`, fake `ISearchClient`, in-memory Dataverse facade.</step>
    <step order="3">Add `SummarizeMatter_EndToEnd_ReturnsCompletedRun` test: author Template via fixture loader; create ActionInstance; POST `/actions/{id}/run`; assert HTTP 200; load `sprk_actionrun` record; assert Status == Completed + audit chain has entries for `QueryDataverse` + `MatterSummary` AI Tool.</step>
    <step order="4">Add `WeeklyTaskDigest_ScheduledDispatch_RendersAndDelivers` test: author scheduled Template; create ActionInstance; invoke `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler.HandleAsync(jobMessage)` directly; use `AutoApproveGateResolver` test override; assert Run completed; assert `SendEmail` Tool was dispatched.</step>
    <step order="5">Add `FindSimilarMatters_Hybrid_RanksWithCitations` test: stub the AI Search client to return 3 candidate results; author Template; invoke; assert results contain matter IDs + similarity rationale + citations; assert audit chain logs both `SearchDocuments` + `QueryDataverse` Tools.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~StarterTemplates` and verify all 3 tests pass. If any fail, fix the test (do not modify production code — that's task 053/054/055 territory).</step>
    <step order="7">Verify ADR-015 compliance: scan assertions for any verbatim prompt or response content; if found, replace with hash-only or shape-only checks. Audit chain assertions check `auditEntry.HashOnly == true` for Tier 2.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj` if new test discovery is needed (typically not required for xUnit).</step>
    <step order="9">Run `dotnet test` (full suite) to confirm no regression in other test suites.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Quality gates skipped per rigor STANDARD (testing tag).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 060 status ✅. Update `current-task.md`: task 060 complete; G1 verified.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviation in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build + test runner</tool>
    <tool name="terminal">Shell commands</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="test">tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ActionEngine/StarterTemplatesIntegrationTests.cs</output>
