  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">**G1**: Three starter Templates author + execute end-to-end via manual and scheduled invocation (verified by `StarterTemplates` test suite passing). All 3 tests in `StarterTemplatesIntegrationTests.cs` PASS via `dotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~StarterTemplates`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every Tool dispatch in the test scenarios writes at least one audit-chain entry (assertion present in each test).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No verbatim prompt/response content appears in test assertions (ADR-015 Tier 2 hash-only respected).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Scheduled-trigger test invokes `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler.HandleAsync(...)` directly without depending on real Service Bus.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Full `dotnet test` suite passes after additions (no regressions).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This task directly verifies graduation gate **G1** from spec.md §Success Criteria #1 and plan.md §7 Acceptance Criteria. The 3 starter Templates are demo surface for product-owner acceptance — failures here block MVP sign-off.

    Use the existing `AnalysisOrchestrationService` integration test as the pattern reference for `WebApplicationFactory` + fake AI clients. Do NOT introduce real Azure OpenAI or Azure AI Search calls in CI — keep everything in-memory.
  </notes>

